To find the Highest Value : SELECT MAX(your_column) AS highest_value FROM your_table;
To find the Min Value: SELECT MIN(column_name) AS min_value FROM table_name;
To find the Top 3 values: SELECT your_column, other_column1, other_column2 FROM your_table ORDER BY your_column DESC LIMIT 3;
To find the Min 3 values: SELECT your_column, other_column1, other_column2 FROM your_table ORDER BY your_column ASC LIMIT 3;



write the SQL query to get the usernames before the @ in the email 
------------------------------------------------------------------
SELECT 
SUBSTRING_INDEX(Email_Id, '@', 1) AS User_Name
FROM Table;
